_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_processing_pipeline", "label": "Intended Processing Pipeline", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_hop_detection_state_machine", "label": "Hop Detection State Machine (STANDING/RISING/AIRBORNE/LANDING)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Modeled as a phased state machine (rising/airborne/landing) rather than a single threshold check so that walking and crouching can be explicitly rejected and exactly one event is emitted per valid hop."}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_turn_around_state_machine", "label": "Turn-Around Detection State Sequence (FRONT/SIDE/BACK/SIDE/FRONT)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Uses accumulated body rotation through front/side/back/side/front classification, with tolerance for temporary landmark loss, so half-turns and side-and-return motions are rejected while full 360-degree turns in either direction are accepted."}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_testing_strategy", "label": "Mandatory Testing Strategy (unit/integration/system/regression/performance)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_plan_format", "label": "Required Phase Plan Format (Section 8)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_completion_report_format", "label": "Required Phase Completion Report Format (Section 9)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_definition_of_done", "label": "Definition of Done", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_continuous_verification_rules", "label": "Continuous Verification Rules", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_agent_responsibilities", "label": "Agent Responsibilities (per-phase plan/approve/implement/report loop)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The agent must present a plan and wait for explicit approval before touching files, then stop after each phase, so that scope stays bounded, tests are never skipped, and the human retains control over architectural changes rather than the agent silently continuing to the next phase."}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_development_principles", "label": "Development Principles (Section 3)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Principles such as keeping platform-specific code out of the shared module, using timestamps instead of assuming a fixed frame rate, avoiding global mutable state, and keeping camera/pose/detection/UI separated exist to keep movement detection deterministic, reproducible, and testable without camera hardware."}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_0", "label": "Phase 0: Repository and Environment Assessment", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_1", "label": "Phase 1: Base Kotlin Multiplatform Project Structure", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_2", "label": "Phase 2: Shared Pose Data Model", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "Plan Files/cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "plan_files_cross_platform_movement_detection_master_plan_phase_3", "label": "Phase 3: Recorded Pose Input and Test Harness", "file